Oil price
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The oil price is increased by 10 percent relative to the baseline.
 This affects all foreign prices both import prices and export competing
 prices.
 The shock affects supply through the prices of intermediate inputs in productio
n.
 It affects demand through increased exports and substitution away from
 imports for given domestic prices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The import price of energy increases a lot, but other foreign prices also
 increase
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Pass-through rigid for both foreign and domestic prices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Substitution away from imports and intermediate inputs makes employment
 increase in the short run
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Wages increase over time, but real wages fall
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Positive short run effect on government budget
\end_layout

