\begin_layout Subsection
Foreign prices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The two driving exogenous prices are increased by 1 percent: The oil price
 and the foreign price excluding direct and indirect effects from the oil
 price.
 The import and export competing prices endogenously follow these prices.
 With some rigidity, all foreign prices increase 1 percent.
 This shock affects supply through the prices of intermediate inputs in
 production and it affects demand through increased exports and substitution
 away from imports for given domestic prices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Pass-through rigid for both foreign and domestic prices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All foreign prices increase 1 percent in the long run
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The shock is expansionary in the short run
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Domestic prices are more rigid and net exports will increase - especially
 in the medium term
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Firms expect this increase and invest in capital in the short run
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Households are net savers and their real wealth is decreased by the shock
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Lower real wealth gives lower real returns, lower real pension income and
 lower real inheritance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All in all this lowers long run real consumption
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Lower long run demand from consumption makes wages grow with slightly less
 than 1 percent in the long run
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Output prices and export prices increase by slightly less than 1 percent
 in the long run
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Exports increase and import decrease in the long run - to compensate for
 lower private consumption
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Positive short run effect on government budget
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Long run effect on government budget and fiscal sustainability is small
\end_layout

